title: Chief Cryptographer
bio: Don Beaver leads cryptographic research and development at Jump Crypto with special attention to scaling cross-chain bridges, reducing trusted points of failure, and managing cross-party min-trust relationships through applications of zero knowledge proofs. He is the creator of "Beaver Triples," the core mechanism used in most modern-day multiparty secret computation protocols. He invented the first decentralized random beacon, launched the field of pseudorandom correlation generators, and published a seminal paper on delegated secret computations including a "multilinear extension" trick which grew into foundational crypto theory (IP=PSPACE, PCPs) and most modern zero-knowledge proof strategies. He coined the "garbled" in "garbled circuits" and the "real vs ideal" approach used in modern cryptographic protocol assurance. Prior to joining Jump in 2022, Don was Staff Research Scientist at Meta FinTech, where he contributed to zero-knowledge projects (Winterfell), privacy applications, and decentralized random beacons (STROBE). Don was co-founding engineer for Apple News and Apple iBooks Author, co-author of Google Dapper (infrastructure observability), and developed UI and ML deployed in Uber self-driving cars. Other roles have included faculty at Penn State University, chair of the IACR Crypto conference and IFCA Financial Cryptography conference, board of directors of the IACR, editorial board for Journal of Cryptology. Don holds an AB in Molecular Biology and a PhD in Computer Science from Harvard.
